Nov 16 2009 	No Complaints....	My husband and I checked in to Trump Las Vegas on Friday, November 13th and stayed for 2 nights. I have to tell you it was great staying at a non-smoking, no casino hotel. The first impression was great. The hotel is very clean and well appointed. Not to over-the-top tacky trump like i was expecting. It was reasonably understated and elegant. I loved not having to wind through a stinky crowded casino to find the front desk to check in. We checked in so quickly and were pleasantly surprised by our great room! We upgraded to a strip view, which for $20 per day was totally worth it. We were on the 47th floor and had a great view down the strip. The room has a kichenette, but not like a kitchenette that you may be thinking. This has a subzero refridge and is sleekly built in against the wall. It was so nice having this amenity. We ended up taking a cab to Vons and got some food and drink for our room It was about a $30 cab ride. Across the street (directly) is the Fashion Show mall, so great! They have an ABC store there that sells some food and drinks. So if you don&quot;t want to go to the market, you can just go here. But we saved so much by having food in our room and not having to use room service once. Not to mention, the housekeepers do your dishes! Okay, the bathroom...it is awesome. The bath tub is huge and doubles as a jacuzzi. There is a television in the mirror, which was a very cool feature. The rooms are nicely appointed and the bed was very comfortable. These rooms are larger than a standard hotel room, as they eventually will be residents for people to purchase. That is how they are designed. More homelike less hotel room like. I am a picky person and have worked in the hospitality industry for years. So i know what to look for and i know what to expect. This property is great and the staff was very attentive. After being out both nights having dinner and doing a little gambling and dancing and walking...it is so nice to re