Oct 30 2009	Five Star Wannabee	This place has got to be bleeding money, and it shows in cleanliness and service. A five star should have impeccable service. Don't expect this at the Trump. No bellman took my bags from my taxi, no doorman held the door for me when I entered the hotel on arrival or any time thereafter. The place is beautiful and the rooms are huge, with great beds and amenities and huge bathrooms with jaccuzi tubs, but my room had very dirty windows and toilet paper that was a step below what you might expect to find in an airport or elementary school. I ate the Sunday breakfast buffet. 27 bucks a person. What a joke. That must be where they are trying to make up money. Trump is non-smoking, a huge bonus, and is a great bargain just off the strip. I would recommend it, especially for bargain minded folks looking for a great deal. But do not expect a five star experience if that is what you are used to. Be aware that this place is noisy, too. Even on the 42nd floor, freeway and train noise was loud. Bring ear plugs.	
