Sep 20 2009 	Not Bad	Booked the hotel thru Priceline.I have both good and bad comments about this hotel. Trump Hotel has exceptional staff, great service, very nice lobby.Location is good and bad, depending on what you are looking for. There is no casino in the hotel, thus it is very quiet, which is great and relaxing, while all other hotels on the strip are all very busy and crowded. Trump is not exactly on the strip, if you do not drive, it takes a bit of a walk. If you drive, valet service is great, and the driveway is pretty wide, thus traffic (valet + cabs) goes by quickly, while other hotels are very crowded and congested. But since there is no casino, there is no self-park, valet is the only option and they charge you $15 +tax resort fee per night to cover the valet and two small bottles of water and access to the pool (pool is pretty small). Personally I do not think it worths the $ comparing to other strip hotels, and it is just a total rip-off if you do not drive. They also charge ~$12 per 24 hours of internet access.Trump is just next by the FashionShow Mall, which is great.Trump is also next to the railway, the train can be a bit noisy. But it did not bother me too much as I was very tired every night after a day of fun and it was not hard to fall asleep. This hotel is rated for 5*, which I would expect everything is in high standard. I feel that part of the hotel is 5* and part of it is not up to the par. Lobby and staff are exceptional, it gives you a 5* feel right away, but I do not feel the same for the room. The design of the air vent is just bad, it keeps rattling the whole night and this keeps us awake, not the loud train. We were given the 49th floor the first night, the next morning, we asked for a room changed. They gave us another room, but it was worse, with duct tape taping the vents (and still hear the rattling sound!) How ugly and just not acceptable! my Hubby went back to the lobby, pass the 2nd room keys back to the staff and without him saying anything, the staff knew we were not happy and asked us to wait. Glady they upgraded us to a 1-bedroom corner suite on the 58th floor. View was amazing. All vent has the same design, but maybe it is on a upper floor, it is not as noisy (and train is not that loud too). So we stayed on this 1-bedroom suite for the remaining nights. Beside the bad ventilation design, other things I feel not to the par is the design of the closet space - with a big room, there aren't too many spaces for our clothes and we got a closet with just a hanger rod with no hangers and no shelves. The other thing is the toilet paper they pick, its so thin and rough. The shower head is not strong enough, and not sure where to hang my towels so i can grab it easily right after shower. The bathroom is huge, but again, there is not much space to put our stuff and it feels like a big empty space, not functional enough. Some part of the wallpaper has bubbles and seems like it is going to peel off soon... However, I have to say the bed is very comfortable, the tv in the mirror in the bathroom is nice, and overall i enjoyed the stay (only because they switch us to a room not that is not noisy). But given the options in Vegas, I would not recommend this hotel to a friend.	
