Sep 10 2009 	Great Rooms well off the Strip	Stayed at the Trump over Labor Day, booked through Priceline, had a great room on the 42nd floor. Large comfortable bed with a kitchenette (which went unused), HD TV, lounge area and a huge bathroom with a jacuzzi tub and TV. The room was very clean though there is maid service only once a day, the staff was friendly and attentive, they got us great seats for Zumanity the same day. There is only valet parking which can take some time during the busy parts of the day and the pool area is packed, so go early if you want a good spot. Though the Trump is right across from Nordstrom and the Fashion Show Mall, it is a pretty good walk to the Strip, the Wynn is probably the closest casino to the Trump. I had no problems with the reported train noise, though my girlfriend said she heard it a few times. Also at checkout, they comped the resort fee and the internet fee for me so that was a nice surprise.	
