Aug 24 2009 	Finally a place in Vegas that we'll return to!	The Trump is the perfect choice for travellers that want to be close to the action on the Strip but who don't want to swim through hordes at the casino resorts just to check-in or return to your room for so r&amp;r. The location was fabulous, within walking distance to the Wynn and right across the road from Nordstroms at the Fashion Mall (which my wife really appreciated!). The building itself - from the lobby through the elevators and common areas to our studio room - was immaculate and spotless (pool is an okay size but who really goes to Vegas to hang at the pool all day, right?). The service was uber-friendly and courteous. Security in the lobby discretely ensures the place is for paying guests only. The DJT restaurant in the lobby is quite good but we enjoyed our meals on the Strip better ... breakfast was overly pricey and not worth a second visit. The only real nit - the mandatory valet service took about 10-15 minutes everytime. It is included in the resort fee, which we thought was reasonable, and the valet staff are great, but self-parking if available would have been our choice. We finally figured out, though, that for shorter non-overnight stops at the hotel to change clothes, take a nap, etc., the trick is to park in the underground parking at Nordstroms and just walk 90 seconds across to the hotel - saved us a bunch of time. All in all, a great value (we picked 5-star at Priceline and paid only $120/night for our Strip view room).	
