our laptop or netbook with you, there is free internet anywhere in the mall. The mall was accessable as early as 8am. Long before the 10am opening time for most of the stores.  The room was beyond what we expected especially with the upgrade at checkin. You couldnt ask for a better view of the strip. From our room, we could see part of the water and light show at The Bellagio amd part of the Volcano light and fire show at The Mirage. Value? Well, for a net price of $89/nite, what more could you ask for in a 5Star with Trumps name on it? That price didnt include the choking casino smoke of the other 5Star hotels on the strip. The Trump is Smoke Free. We didnt use the on site restaurant. We did use some of the restaurants in othe hotels. The Bellagio Breakfast Buffet for 18.95 is Incredible. What a great way to start your day. We also took a 10minute drive to Hash House a GoGo on Sahara blvd for breakfast. They were featured on an episode of &quot;Man Vs Food&quot;. The food was incredible and the portions tremendous.We'd recommend The Trump	
