May 21 2009 	Unique no-casino no-smoking hotel-- a haven from the strip	We stayed here 5/14-16. There is a $15 resort fee and $14 parking fee. Hotel is nice and quiet with clean air. My daughters thought they saw Clinton from &quot;What Not to Wear&quot; while we were there, and I wouldn't be surprised if the Trump is popular with celebrities as it has such an insulated, peaceful atmosphere as compared with the casino hotels. It is difficult to walk to the strip due to the lack of crosswalks and sidewalks in the area. From experience, I think the best way is to cross directly from the Trump porte cochere to Nordstrom's porte cochere (entering through the men's department), walk straight through (go around escalators) and you will see a mall map straight ahead. We would usually walk to Neiman Marcus and exit near the Tickets4Less storefront. Once outside, turn right and walk to LV Blvd, &quot;the strip.&quot; There is a bus stop right in front of the mall for the double-decker &quot;Deuce&quot; buses. These are the tourists' best friends as they stop up and down the strip and even go downtown to Fremont. Fare is exact-change-only!! Prices are $3 one way, $7 for 24-hour unlimited pass, and $15 for 3-day unlimited pass.Tickets4less is a good source for show and meal tix, but check the best prices online before buying. One of their best values is a $2 coupon which gets you Harrah's Flavor's buffet for 1/2 price ($8 for lunch, $18? for supper which includes bottomless soda/milk/juice). They had snow crab legs when we went for supper but it was overcooked. We thought the lunch was fabulous though.We got stuck in the Trump's elevator during our trip, and the management was very apologetic and compensated us for our trouble.In the evening, it is imperative to return to Trump through the mall or take a taxi at night if you aren't fast on your feet or can't see well. Drivers speed down the street at night, and it is curvy and dark, without sidewalks or crosswalks.	
