r provide new shampoo and other toiletries.This was the service provided after we told them we discovered blood on our sheets. I can't image what it would be like without the front desk's personal guarantee that they would ensure the room was cleaned.When I checked out I told the front desk that I was not satisfied with my stay at the hotel. They looked at my account and told me that they had removed the $15 spa charge (This fee is a whole other issue, but something I know hotels charge) as compensation for finding blood on the bedding issue. I never was contacted by a manager or customer service representative to discuss what happen. If the Trump International was presenting itself as a One or Two star hotel, maybe I could understand. However, they state they are a 5 star hotel. Even, without the room service issues this hotel is a very bad choice for Las Vegas.	
