Apr 3 2009 	Great Experience! Service was Outstanding in Every Department!	I booked thru Priceline for March 27-29, hoping to get any other 5 Star Resort so I was disappointed to get Trump. It turned out to be perfect. We arrived early after driving in from Murrieta, CA. You exit Spring Mountain. Stay in the left lane of the off-ramp. After valeting, we waited in a short line to check in. I asked to be away from the train and have a pool view. She put us in unit 5728, on the 57th floor with a direct view high above the city with a perfect strip view. Amazingly, we could hear the train during the day, but never noticed it at night. We were able to see the Bellagio water show. Before the wife and I had a chance to finish bringing in our belongings, the kids were so excited about the jucuzzi tub. Be warned, just add alot less shampoo than you normally would for a bubble bath. With the jets on, it made a mountain of bubbles and the kids could hide in it. The unit was top-notch. The maid service was perfect. Everything was replenished, dishes washed, even the sofa bed was made up for us. Put the minifridge on the coldest level and your drinks will get cold fast and freeze. The pool area wasn't impressive, just functional. It was heated though and the kids still had alot of fun. Service there was also very nice. A life guard grabbed us towels and escorted us to a large, padded lounger that could fit several people. When the pool closed, they allowed us to keep the kids wrapped up in the pool towels up to the room instead of having to return the towels at the pool and have the kids go up cold. The kids ages are 6, 4 and almost 2. The hotel is non-smoking and we really appreciated breathing clean air. By the way, the lobby area smells great. Sounds weird, but you notice it. Walk into some Vegas hotels and you think you're gonna leave with lung cancer. About the walk to the strip. Are you kidding? Its 5 minutes max. Think about this. Stay at any of the mega resorts, and its a hike to the elavator from your room, then thru the casino before you get to the strip. Its probably about the same time. Most of us are gluttons while in Vegas and could use the walk to burn a few calories anyway. The location is great because you have the convenience of the mall across the street and 5 star resorts like Encore, Wynn, Palazzo, and Venetian very close by. Check-out was smooth, no hidden fees, just the expected resort fee. The valet wait wasn't long at all and we checked out on a Sunday. My brothers were at the Encore, checked out on a Monday, and waited for a half hour for their vehicle. After driving away, we realized we left some clothes hanging in the closet. We called the Trump, turned around, and the maid had already prepared it for security to bring down to us. It was truly a perfect overall experience. For Hotwire users, Hotwire has a separate 5 star condo central strip category and 5 star hotel category. The Trump is the 5 star condo. That may change when City Center and other projects finish. We'll be back, the value is great and the service even greater.	
