outside and walk the strip a bit. You certainly can't do that from The Trump.All in all, I would choose another hotel despite this one's beauty, because of the resort fee - service issues and the location would reaffirm my choice.	
Feb 22 2009 	Excellent Hotel But....	The Trump is an excellent choice in LV. It's luxurious and quiet (no casino) but close to all the action. Great views from all the rooms.The only problem is the freight train that passes by on the west side of the hotel. At exactly 4:45AM each day, I was awakened by the blast of a steam whistle from the train. Then, I waited for each of the cars to pass by (clickety-clack.) Then when I was back asleep, another train came by at 6:00AM. The train noise coupled with the traffic noise (I had a great view of the highways and the Erotic Heritage Museum) made for difficult sleeping. So, luxury does have some drawbacks. The Trump is a bargain, however, for the type of quality room you get; marble tiling &amp; high-end furnishings. It is also the only hotel that charges for parking in LV, how cheap can you be? Get your room on the east side!	
