Feb 13 2009 	Not Bad for $89 plus $15 resort fee	Just finished a 10 day stay at the Trump: Overall the hotel is clean and comfortable with rooms that are well designed. My business partner had a one bedroom suite which has a complete kitchen with Wolf Stove top, Sub Zero Fridge and Wolf oven. The room also has a table that seats 4 and an “L” shaped sectional. My studio had a kitchenette with a small Sub Zero and a two burner Wolf top and a comfortable seating area. The rooms connect via a common entrance which is nice so you can open up both rooms and still maintain your privacy. Some negative things people should be aware of before booking:1. The hotel does not disclose a $15 per day “resort fee”2. Internet access is $11.99 per day3. Phone access via the hotel land line has a connection charge of $12 for the first minute, plus a huge per minute fee. The rates are not disclosed in the room. After a few words with management they did remove the near $100 charge. 4. Hotel staff does not obey the “do not disturb” sign, I was awoken several times.5. In Suite Dining (room service) overprice and poor food quality and taste. 6. Only one restaurant and bar, no Casino7. Not enough staff for check in/out 8. TRAIN which blows its horn 4-5 times per night, my room was facing Industrial Ave and the Love Boutique. Overall it is an incredible value for $89 per night plus the $15 resort fee.	
