Dec 12 2008	Luxury Living - A home from Home	For us this hotel had everything, we were in Las Vegas to see the sights, the Hoover Dam and the Grand Canyon. The Hotel is just off the strip but only a short cab ride or 10 minute walk from most of the casinos, the Trump does not have a casino, but this was a plus for us, we were not interested in gambling every day. We just wanted a comfortable base and the Trump was very comfortable.The hotel has a nice reception area, most if the staff were friendly; all the staff were helpful and professional. (just one maid who did not clean the room very well on one of the days, so she did not get a tip) Generally we felt very welcome throughout our stay.The bar was nice; the gentleman serving on the bar was very attentive to everyone, very professional, even got to try a few new drinks.There was a nice gym and swimming pool, the area was clean and tidy with a good selection of sun loungers with a plentiful supply of towels.We did have a small problem with the room when we first checked in, I have a feeling some previous guests had trashed the room. (The room itself was fantastic but there was a smell of damp.) We spoke to reception, there was no quibble, and they could not have been more apologetic, they told us that the carpets had been washed and this maybe the problem.They asked us if we would mind moving and said they would upgrade us to a suite by way of apology.The suite was fantastic, it had every amenity, kitchen with cooker, freezer, and dishwasher, bar area and dining/sitting areas, plasma type screens in both the dinning and bedroom. The bed was very comfortable, my partner and myself had a great nights sleep, the air conditioning was great throughout the property.The bathroom was fantastic, to our amusement there was a television inset into the bathroom mirror, there were plenty of fluffy towels, dressing gowns and slippers, his and hers sinks, whirlpool bath. The whole property was well maintained.The staff on the door were great, always happy to help, calling taxis or giving advice, looking after luggage etc.The only negative is that the railway line runs quite close to the hotel and the trains blast their whistle/horn while going through the level crossing. This could be disturbing to some. The hotel is just across the road from the mall, so a shopper’s paradise and if you love your food there are plenty of places to eat nearby. The hotel does have its own restaurant but we did not use this.We felt this we received great value at this accommodation, I would certainly return and do recommend this accommodation to my friends.	
