Sep 1 2008 	Nice Rooms but boring hotel.	My wife and I stayed at the new Trump Las Vegas in late August. Overall the Hotel is very nice. The service is good, the lobby is beautiful and the rooms are excellent. Every room is large and comes equipped with a fully functioning kitchen. The bathrooms are great, they have huge showers and jacuzzi tubs. The beds are very very comfortable. The pool was descent size, with lots of chairs, but very boring and uneventful. The location of the Hotel is good. It is a little off the strip, by the Fashion Show Mall across from the Wynn Hotel. The Trump is great, but it has no energy. It would seem like a nice place to stay for a person in Vegas on business or an extended stay. The Trump just does not have any Vegas feel. Staying at the Trump has the same energy of staying at an airport hotel but with high class amenities. I would suggest staying at the Wynn or Venetian instead, the rooms are about the same but the those Hotels have a great Vegas vibe to them. Overall, a great luxury experience but with no sense of enegy.	
Aug 31 2008 	Some improvements required	Room 2817: Toilet seat was broken. Room door and the door from hallway to anteroom did not always close completely if just released without further pushing against the door. In fact, once we came back and noticed the room door was not fully closed after housekeeping (I was able to push it open without the use of the key). In addition the doors are very loud. This also applies to the toilet door and the shower door. Service of housekeeping can be improved (coffee powder was not refilled, blankets for the crib were replaced but not put on). Valet service was quite slow (long waits for the car). Would have liked to be offered a bottle of water during wait (as seen at the MGM Signature last year).	
Aug 29 2008 	Friendly quite and comfortable hotel to stay in Vegas	We stayed at the Trump International for two days at the end of 2 weeks road trip to visit some national parks in that area.I have two reservations with the hotel, one for each night (we first thought that we will only stay here for one night). When I checked in at 2pm in the afternoon, the front-desk guy couldn't find my reservation for that night (he found the reservation for second night). Luckily, I have the reservation printed out, he called Hotels.com, and got it sort out. He was very friendly, and upgraded me to a suite with strip view on high floor for my patience. The lobby is nicely decorated, and very quite compare to other hotels on strip; the room is very clean, and comfortable; the bathroom is amazing, I was impressed by the build-in flat TV on the mirror in bathroom even though I didn't use it much; the pool is good, but the pool at the Bellagio is way better. The people there are very friendly, and service are very good at the hotel. We decided not to have the house keeping work done the first day there, and they called us late in the afternoon to check on that. The wake up call even tells you the weather forecast too (I think it was a real person's voice too, but I could be wrong, since it was in the early morning).I only have two negative things about the hotel: parking and fitness center. I found out there is no self-parking, and it costs you $14 a day to park there. I was trying to use fitness center, and found out that it would cost you $22 to use it. Yup, $22, of course you are allowed to use some spa facilities, but I just want to do some weights :(	
Aug 28 2008 	Dont' stay here	I stayed for 6 nights at the Trump in the middle of August. Comments then review below:Atmosphere:- Has a fancy lobby but seemed to have few guests, few staff and generally felt dead during my 6-nights thereRooms:- very soft, sponge-like beds- nice bathroom, good jacuzzi bath- well appointed with brand-name kitchen appliances - some rooms are very noisy (soundproofing inadequate to mask the freight trains passing by throughout the night)Facilities:- no room service- no bottled water in room (!)- no mini bar in room- expensive internet access- lobby bar is dead- the highly-rated restaurant (DTR) closed in July. Wouldnt surprise me if the whole hotel follows soon- didnt use pool- no smoking throughoutLocation:- very top of strip- opposite fashion show mall which is good for shopping and has a food court- taxis avoid it so you often have to cross the road to get one (and you will always need taxis from this hotel)Review:I used to discount 1 star reviews, but now after writing one I will be sure to read them!This was my first time to Vegas and I expected great things from a Trump-branded hotel. I was let down from the start. When checking in I told reception that I was shattered after flying on two planes for 15 hours to get there. So they put me in room 1613 where the freight trains woke me up every hour or two through the night. Good hotels, at a minimum, guarantee guests good night's sleep; the Trump can't even do that. What's worse is that when I told them I wanted to move rooms there was no apology, just a knowing-expression... considering that the hotel was pretty much empty, why would they even put guests into substandard rooms? To be fair, my new room on the 44th floor almost muted out the trains.Feel like a glass of water during the night? Unlucky no water is provided. Feel like a snack? Unlucky - no room service. In fact there is not even a mini bar. Feel like a good meal in your hotel? Unlucky, the respected restaurant has closed down. Feel like walking somewhere interesting from the hotel? Unlucky - there's only the mall opposite. Cross the road to the mall to get a taxi - they dont go there voluntarily.DONT THINK YOU ARE GETTING A GREAT DEAL BY STAYING HERE - For the same price as a room in the Trump you could take one of the best rooms in one of the strip casinos and actually be in Vegas. You will also get points towards that casino's players club (and may even end up getting your room, shows or food for free). Most importantly you will be in a place which has something going for it..	
Aug 22 2008 	A Little Piece of Quiet	If you want to be able to go downstairs and gamble, this hotel is not for you. There is no casino. However, after three days at the loud, smoky and tourist ridden Bellagio, the Trump was like heaven. There were no crowds, the staff was extraordinarily courteous and helpful, no noise from the casino and no smoke! As a matter of fact, the place smells wonderful. They blow some kind of fresh scent through the vents! We were greeted with cold water and to get to our room, we had to only walk through the lobby. Our room was on the 59th floor with a fabulous view of the south Strip. The room was lovely and clean with a small, fully equipped kitchen. It did not, however, have a minibar, so if thirsty, we had to go to the store in the lobby. I will add the the location is a bit peculiar, and not super handy for walking around (especially in the summer heat), but we had a car,and the valets were very quick, so it was not an issue for us. We took at taxi to the Venetian one night and it was less than $5.00. As stated above, if you are going and want your Vegas experience to be the traditional noisy, crowded, smoky one, you will not like the Trump. However, if you enjoy a respite from the commotion, the Trump is fantastic.	
Aug 19 2008 	Peaceful Oasis!	My wife and I stayed at the Trump from Aug. 8-10 and found the hotel to be beyond our expectations. I had warned her that the hotel had no casino, no choice of restaurants, and was a 5-7 minute walk from the strip, but she still loved it. After spending the day trying to squeeze past crowds in the other hotels and inhaling pungent cigar smoke, it was nice to come back to a hotel that smelled like flowers and was always quiet. The staff is extremely friendly and helpful. They will go out of their way to make your stay more enjoyable. Two things to note that we didn't like. First, the pool closes at 6pm which is absolutely ridiculous. It's 95-100 degrees in Vegas all summer. it would be nice to be able to take a swim in the evening to cool off and unwind. Second, it is very convenient to cut through the mall to get to the strip during the day, but at night, when the mall is closed, it can be a little dangerous trying to navigate your way back down the street with cars whizzing by and no consistent path for safety. I hope they address this and build a walkway to the strip for patrons. As for the room itself, it is heaven! The bed is the most comfortable you will find anywhere and the bathroom is a woman's dream! Double marble sinks, a jacuzzi tub, a huge shower, and a separate area for the toilet. Don't forget about the built-in 17&quot; LCD TV in the mirror! The room also has double doors so that hallway noise does not pass into your room..great idea! I must admit that the train that most people complained about does wake you up around 8:30am but it wasn't a big deal for us since we wanted to get up early to take advantage of the day anyway. If you're concerned about it, ask for a room on the highest floor possible or get a strip view room on the other side.	
Aug 12 2008 	Trump International was a super stay!	My wife and I stayed at Trump International from August 4th to August 10th. The hotel was immaculate and the service was great! There was no casino, but the walk to the nearest casino was so small, it didn't matter.  The room was cleaned daily, was beautiful and we had a great view. The bathroom was especially nice. I have nothing negative to say about the Trump International. I would easily stay here again. It is 5 stars all the way! I guess the only small negative is the restaurant in the hotel is a little pricey, but you can eat just minutes away, so that was a non-issue.	
Aug 11 2008	The Donald is being cheap.	My husband and I travel extensively on business throughout the US. We are in Vegas 2-3 times per year for various retail trade shows. We are not smokers or gamblers and thought that Trump Int'l would be perfect for us. Well the room is quite comfortable, however be prepared for the hidden costs. There is no self-parking only Valet thus be prepared to tip constantly. Although the in room kitchen is lovely, complimentary coffee is given to you only once. If you want more coffee, it will cost $6.00 per package which makes 2 cups. Toiletries are only replaced once. Please bring your own shampoo etc. For a five star hotel they are being very cheap. Why give me a sub zero refrigerator and charge me to brew coffee in the room? It doesn't make sense. We have stayed at various hotels on the strip and will not return here. I think the Venetian has better rooms, pool and amenities for the price. Sorry Donald.	
